latestPosts.caption:
It’s never too late to pursue what sets your soul on fire. ❤️

The journey hasn’t been easy. I spent six years in the corporate world before moving to NYC, where I couldn’t work under my visa at the time. I had plans to start a tattoo apprenticeship in Toronto, but like many dreams, mine got delayed by the pandemic.

Eventually, I began apprenticing in New York during my free time—and now, I’m proud to say I’m a tattoo artist working in a city that many artists only dream of.

My path has been anything but straightforward, but if there’s one thing I’ve learned, it’s this: with passion and persistence, you can create a life you love. 

Thank you to everyone who has been a part of my journey so far. You all make my life a whole lot more bright ♥️
.
